rComments: great prof but none of what we learn in class is useful for the exam. Exam preparation is just a memorization exercise and he is very picky with his questions. He will ask you questions on topics that you would think are irrelevant in the textbook. Make sure you study hard for this one!

Exams are pretty difficult. He makes the course less boring but he will kill you on the exams. Exams are 90% text based, 10% lecture based but he'll test you on the LITTLEST details in the book. Pretty much memorize the book and you're guaranteed a 60... the rest, may God be with you!

This professor is extremely approachable! Has a good scene of humor. His slides are unique and he loves to engage students in class through discussions and personal experiences. I recommend this professor to all management students enrolled in any of his classes!

Had him in Summer '09. He's very approachable, friendly and understanding. HEAVY if not all textbook use + a few lecture notes. Exams are hard for students bc they involve heavy memorization. Extremely fair at marking presentations/assignments. Overall, loved his class .. OB can be quite dry, but I enjoyed it! His accent is fully understandable. :)
Good prof exams were not hard at all.  Classes are fun and easy to follow, Read the text and know it well. Harder to get than the president.
